<sentence id="6">Streptolysin O is a cytotoxin that damages human tissue and increases host cell cytotoxicity [ 7,25 ] .</sentence>
<sentence id="7">The resulting cellular damage , particularly to polymorphonuclear leukocytes [ 26 ] , decreases internalization and subsequent intracellular killing of streptococci [ 27 ] .</sentence>
